[thinking] I'm thinking about how version 3.0 changes environment behavior. If there's meaningful coverage, I wonder if it should involve the variable source needing environment variables. It's interesting that no fixed external environment is required. I’m also noticing that tests can set system properties using System.setProperty, but environment variables are trickier to set. We might need to look into using withEnvironment. Inspecting the source seems important here as well.
[thinking] 
